{
  "texts": [
    "This system, comprising five key units, serves as a model for many countries.",
    "It encompasses diagnosis, profilisation, and career guidance; military mental support services; assistance for the demobilized; aid for civilian populations; and support for families of victims.",
    "Rehabilitation program for reintegration is of particular note.",
    "It includes measures aimed at preparing relatives of the members of the armed forces for their returning home, develops rehabilitation programs, establishes or sustains anonymous help centers, and provides maintenance to the members of the armed forces with diverse needs.",
    "Ukraine can use this experience to enhance its own assistance system for military personnel and veterans (Shvets et al., 2021)."
  ]
}